tunic, fbss, other nice gear, he was using a 2hb.. can't remember but it was deadly <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  i noticed however that that must have been the only weapon he had ever used, (when I disarmed him, he was lucky to hit me for 1 even) Anyway..<br>
I had no buffs, He had none that I know of, however when my SBD proced, I ran back and got sow (from one of my sow potions) and charged back in...<br>
the fight lasted long enough for him to use mend 3 times <br>
at the end he was down to half a bubble when I finally died ..<br>
I started off with some poison.. asp I think(just one I had on me at the time)<br>
<br>
anyway, any hints for fighting people(specially monks) that are that well eqiuped?<br>
<br>
BTW I had Burning rapier, SBD combo going...<br>
Now that I think of it, I should have broke out my gnoll whip for stuns <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
He was an iksar, so he had the ac bonus*2 i think and more regen than just fungi if iksar regen stacks with fung<br>
<br>
I mashed down Disarm everytime it popped same with ID, he resisted all my ID's though =\<br>
<br>
any tips are welcome <p><DIV ID=DL STYLE="POSITION:RELATIVE; WIDTH=40%; COLOR:RED; FILTER:WAVE(COLOR=CYAN)"><B><FONT SIZE="3">Gntik Littleblade<B></FONT><BR>Gnomish rogue of Ayonae Ro  <BR> () warden ()</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uchamelionironfists.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ChamelionIronfists</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/29/01 2:41:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fighting people w/ fungi?</span><hr size=1> Don't fight monks well equiped until you are equally equiped.<br>
<br>
Equipment &gt; all <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucoyoteblack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>coyoteblack</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/29/01 5:38:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fighting people w/ fungi?</span><hr size=1> Weaken poison can make him encombered there by messing up his ac bonus. Circle Strafe to land in backstabs. <p>" No matter how subtle the wizard, a knife between the shoulder blades will seriously cramp his style"  -- Vlad Taltos</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulirintz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lirin TZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/29/01 10:08:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fighting people w/ fungi?</span><hr size=1> coyote, he is a monk.  if twinked as much as he says, thats probobly 150 or so str.  a monks weight is 14(?)base and it dosnt go up much more than that.  weaken wont encumber him at all. <p><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=86678>Liringlas Lookinglass</a><br>
Bard of the 51st  Song<br><a href=mrfixitonline.com/patron>Patron Saints</a>
<br>
Fennin Ro
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uchamelionironfists.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ChamelionIronfists</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/29/01 10:41:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fighting people w/ fungi?</span><hr size=1> Hmm, you can try opening with a snare poison.  Then run away since he is snared and apply a slow poison.  Once slow sticks run away and apply a blind poison.  Hit him with that and BS until he is un-blinded.  If he is still snared, then run away and apply another blind.  If snare breaks while hes blinded, apply a new snare right away.  If snare breaks after blind has worn off, melee him.  You should be able to take him now that you slowed him.<br>
<br>
*Almost Forgot*<br>
<br>
Pick up a Slime Coated Harpoon.. 10/25 for 500-800pp if you have the money.  Try trading your BR for one or SBD and 300pp. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uchamelionironfists.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ChamelionIronfists</A> at: 9/29/01 10:43:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utakaraetaekmoor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Takarae Taekmoor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/30/01 12:37:33 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/Takarae/fullsize/thief.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fighting people w/ fungi?</span><hr size=1> erm...br is no drop.   Unless you mean something other than Burning Rapier. <p><center>~<b>Takarae Taekmoor</b>~<BR>
