</font></center></b></p> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uswipey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swipey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/01 3:37:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Fighting people w/ fungi?</span><hr size=1> On a related note, I have a level 1 rogue.  Ive just started him on RZ. Any suggestions as to how i fight the level 5 guy who has Chloroplast from his High level friend there, and a trak tooth in hand?  Any time I get more than 50' from the guards he attacks me.  If I hang out near the guards too much he talks trash and eventually his High level friend kites the guards off and he attacks me.<br>
<br>
Oh, and every time I log in He and his friend are there, sometimes they just have different names. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uswipey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swipey</A> at: 10/1/01 3:44:10 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/01 10:52:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fighting people w/ fungi?</span><hr size=1> If he doesn't have see invis you should be able to snare poison him hide apply blind poison and then kill him fairly easily no matter how much better his equipment is. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustorntranquilfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Storn Tranquilfist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=" http://www.dbzgtlegacy.com/dbzaimicons/vegeta.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/5/01 5:03:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fighting people w/ fungi?</span><hr size=1> OK, I'm a monk and I know what I hate <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Hide will be excellent, Blind will be great and same with snare poison. A decent ID skill would rock too. First thing, get the snare poison to stack then ID him, He'll run off feared and you Can keep BSing/Hitting him, then you should blind/BS, hope this info helps you. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=798 "> <img src="http://www.strike9.com/eq/Stornn/fullsize/finalsig.jpg" border="0" alt="Click to See my Profile"></a>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uceescritdabossalini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceescrit da Bossalini</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/8/01 9:20:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fighting people w/ fungi?</span><hr size=1> Get your own funig :P<br>
<br>
<br>
Seriously though, pre-50 fungi tunics on melees are seriously unbalaning, unless you yourself can put out some serious dmg output.  Also, sounds like he had a tranquil staff (usually fungi twink monks with a big 2 hander does).  Those are damn mean in PvP, if you can joust decently.<br>
<br>
My best advice for your situation would have been to use root poison (the haste debuff is nice), joust him in between blows, and hope you land all of yours, and he misses all of his.  Your only hope would be to out damage his regen, and land some big backstabs to help finish him off.<br>
<br>
My rogue at level 35 has been known to take out even-con fungi twink monks in the past, but its damn hard.  I was in full ravenscale, using an SCH and SBD combo at the time also.  So it is possible if you can time your blows right, and keep from getting hit.<br>
<br>
On a side note, beserker madness is an evil DoT that will seriously outdamage the Fungal regen.  The downside is, it gives a huge STR and a haste buff (I think).  If you get hit, its gonna hurt. <p><font size=4 face=Times New Roman, serif><b>Ceescrit Bossalini</font><BR>
